  "texts": [
    "The Llama model serves as the base LLM, responsible for generating responses based on the input queries and the information provided by the retrieval module.",
    "The reverse proxy layer acts as an intermediary, intercepting queries from the Llama model and directing them to the retrieval module.",
    "The retrieval module is designed to interface with various external data sources, perform searches based on the intercepted queries, and return the most relevant information to the reverse proxy layer.",
    "The reverse proxy layer then enriches the original queries with the retrieved information and forwards them back to the Llama model for final response generation.To illustrate the data flow within the system, consider an example query submitted to the Llama model.",
    "Upon receiving the query, the reverse proxy layer intercepts it and forwards it to the retrieval module."
  ],
